	<h1>
MIE holds annual Design & Awards Day
</h1>
	<div class="page-title-hline">&nbsp;</div>
	










<!-- MAIN CONTENT AREA - START -->



		<div class="floatright">
			<br class="hide" />
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="sidebar" --><!-- FCKEDITOR_sidebar --><!-- /FCKEDITOR_sidebar --> <!-- InstanceEndEditable -->

<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="Sidebar" --><!-- InstanceEndEditable --><br class="hide" />
			</div>


			<div class="contentcolumn">
				<br class="hide" />
<!-- InstanceBeginEditable name="maincontent" --><!-- FCKEDITOR_maincontent --><!-- /FCKEDITOR_maincontent -->

	<div id="entry-132">
		<div class="entry-header">
			<!--<h2 class="asset-name entry-title">
MIE holds annual Design & Awards Day
</h2>-->
			<div class="entry-meta" title="2010-04-14T12:14:28-05:00">Wednesday Apr 14, 2010</div>
		</div>
	
		<div class="entry-content">
			<div class="entry-body">
				
On Tuesday, April 13, the <a href="http://www.me.concordia.ca/">Department of Mechanical and Industrial Engineering</a> (MIE) held its Annual Design &amp; Awards Day Ceremony. Professors, students, and undergraduates gathered for the special event, which honours overall academic achievement, excellence in teaching, and the best Capstone projects by students in the Department. <br /><br /><object width="400" height="300"> <param name="flashvars" value="offsite=true&amp;lang=en-us&amp;page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157623853328924%2Fshow%2F&amp;page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157623853328924%2F&amp;set_id=72157623853328924&amp;jump_to=" /> <param name="movie" value="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" /> <param name="allowFullScreen" value="true" /><embed type="application/x-shockwave-flash" src="http://www.flickr.com/apps/slideshow/show.swf?v=71649" allowfullscreen="true" flashvars="offsite=true&lang=en-us&page_show_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157623853328924%2Fshow%2F&page_show_back_url=%2Fphotos%2Fencs-concordia%2Fsets%2F72157623853328924%2F&set_id=72157623853328924&jump_to=" width="400" height="300"></object><br /><br /><a href="http://users.encs.concordia.ca/%7Epugh/"><b>Martin Pugh</b></a> opened the awards ceremony with a warm welcome to all those assembled. "Today's the day when we celebrate the fact that MIE is the best department in all of Concordia!" Pugh joked. He then handed the mic over to the event's MC, <a href="http://users.encs.concordia.ca/%7Edolat/"><b>Ali Dolatabadi</b></a>, Associate Professor in MIE. The teaching awards were up first. Andrew DiLullo, President of the Concordia chapter of IIE presented <a href="http://users.encs.concordia.ca/%7Ebhuiyan/"><b>Nadia Bhuiyan</b></a> with the IIE Award for Teaching Excellence. Then, Percival Graham, VP Academic of CSME presented a surprised and delighted <b><a href="http://www.me.concordia.ca/facultyandstaff/full-timefaculty/nabil-esmail.php">Nabil Esmail</a></b> with the CSME Award for Teaching Excellence.<br /><br />After the honoured teachers had said their thank-yous, Martin Pugh came back to the podium to present Certificates of Appreciation for Service to the Department to individuals who had recently celebrated 10, 15, 20, or 25 year anniversaries with MIE. <b>Tiahne Wen</b>, <b>Brandon Gordon</b>, and <b>Ibrahim Hassan</b> were given certificates for 10 years.<b> Leslie Hosein </b>and <b>Kudret Demirli</b> were recognized for 15 years of service. <b>Dan Juras</b> ("our barman!" joked Pugh) celebrated 20 years with MIE. And finally departmental denizens <a href="http://concave.concordia.ca/"><b>Subhash Rakheja</b></a> and <a href="http://mediarelations.concordia.ca/mediaresources/featuredresearcher/archives/featured/dr_george_vatistas_1.php"><b>George Vatistas</b></a> were singled out for their quarter century anniversaries. Martin Pugh wrapped up this section of the ceremony by warmly thanking all Administrative, Professional and Technical Staff, regardless of how long they had been there, for their unwavering assistance, noting "I couldn't do my job at all without your support."<br /><br />MIE professors then handed out the Certificates of Merit for Undergraduate Student Involvement in Extracurricular Activities Through Student Associations to <b>Andrew Di Lullo</b>, President of <a href="http://iie.ecaconcordia.ca/">IIE</a>; <b>Marc Koyess</b>, President of <a href="http://csme.ecaconcordia.ca/">CSME</a>; <b>Michael Rembacz</b>, <a href="http://www.concordiasae.ca/">SAE</a> Formula Team Leader ; and <b>Khalid Koraitem</b> founding member of AIAA. The CSME Gold Medal was presented by Ali Dolatabadi to <b>Percival Graham</b> for his outstanding work for that organization; and the Silas Katz Memorial Scholarship was given to <b>Jason Paul Marcus</b> by George Vatistas, who fondly remembered the eponymous founder. Overall undergraduate and graduate student achievements throughout the 2009-10 academic year were warmly acknowledged by Ali Dolatabadi, who invited <a href="http://users.encs.concordia.ca/%7Ewoodadam/">Paula Wood-Adams</a> to the podium to distribute the Graduate Fellowship Awards to deserving ENCS grad students.<br /><br />After this, Henry Hong came up to announce the winners of the Richard Cheng Design Award for Mechanical Engineering. These were: <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;<br /><ul><li><b>Design and Construction of an Atomic Force Microscope&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </b><br />Members: Stephen Dickison, Rafael Arturo Insignares Fernandez, Sarah Halliburton,
 Gregory Lodge Kramer, Stefan Marchant&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <br />Supervisor: Rolf Wuthrich</li></ul><ul><li><b>Design of an Experimental Setup for the Evaluation of Blunt Traumatic Aortic Rupture</b><b>&nbsp;&nbsp; </b><br />Members: Paulo Da Silva, Sara Fawal, Jennifer Goehring, Niloofar 
Moradi-Khaniabadi, Patrick Sardilli, Martin Sosa&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />Supervisor: Lyes Kadem</li></ul>It was then time for the team awards in honour of the outstanding Capstone projects put together by final-year undergraduate students. Engineering Design Specialist for MIE, Dominic Ng, presented the Capstone Design Awards for Mechanical Engineering. These went to the following teams:<br /><br /><ul><li><b>Experimental Setup for the Evaluation of Mitral Prosthetic Heart Valves</b><br />Members: Andrey Bunames, Tamarah Gillis, Carina Groombridge, Constantine Petropoulos, Minh Quan Pham, Laurie-Anne Sobey, Christian Tchozoyema<br />Supervisor: Lyes Kadem</li><li><b>Formula SAE</b><br />Members: Steven Brathwaite, Paul Apostolos Makrisopoulos, Garrett Morgan, Michael Rembacz, Christopher Renaud, Steven Santeusanio, Anthony Sarno<br />Supervisor: Hoi Dick Ng<br /></li></ul><br />Certificates of Merit for Capstone - Mechanical Engineering were presented to:<br /><b><br /></b><ul><li><b>Icing Wind Tunnel</b><br />Members: Ali Aziz, Jeffrey Fortin-Simpson, Percival Graham, Steven Micheli, Justin Rotondo, Toka Zaini<br />Supervisor: Ali Dolatabadi</li><li><b>Electrical Control Finishing Setup</b><br />Members: Constantino Arkali, Simon Ho Chan, Suman Dutta, Reza Khajehmiraki, Muhammad Munir Rohimun <br />Supervisor: Rolf Wuthrich</li><li><b>Table-Top Micro-Factory for Glass Micro-Maching</b><br />Members: Jonathan Burn, Kristina Cook, Wilson Lee, Astrid Olmos, Demetrios Petropoulos, Raymond Taza<br />Supervisor: Rolf Wuthrich<br /></li></ul>The Capstone Design Award for Industrial Engineering went to the  <b>Aveos</b> project by Hend Aziz, Omar Murywed, Cedrick Laporte-Roy, 
Maia Zarmair, Tameem Aswad, Ali Youssef; Supervisor: Dr. Chen;and the Certificate of Merit for Capstone - Industrial Engineering was won by the <b>Hema-Quebec </b>project by Omar Benali, Martha Paola Calderon, Hadeel
 Elchayeb, Maryam Ashkani, Nazim Choudhury, Nabeel Sbei; Supervisor: Dr.
 Kuzgunkaya; <br /><br />The ceremony wrapped up with surprise recognition from all MIE members for <b>Martin Pugh</b>, who was praised for his four years of outstanding leadership as Department Chair. A warm congratulations from ENCS to all the MIE winners and nominees!

<div style="margin-top: 10px; height: 15px;" class="zemanta-pixie"><br /><span class="zem-script more-related pretty-attribution"><script type="text/javascript" src="http://static.zemanta.com/readside/loader.js" defer="defer"></script></span></div>

